Herbie Accessors#

üèó Some features are under construction

Herbie comes with custom xarray DataSet accessors.

# Usage
ds.herbie.<method>

Some of these tools require the Carpenter Workshop package.

[1]:

from herbie import Herbie

[3]:

H = Herbie('2022-12-05 06:00', fxx=6, model='hrrr')
ds = H.xarray("TMP:2 m")

    Cartopy Coordinate Reference System#

    Derive the Cartopy coordinate reference system.

    This is helpful if you want to plot the data on the map.

    Requires Metpy and Pygrib

    [6]:

    ds.herbie.crs

    [6]:

    <cartopy.crs.LambertConformal object at 0x000001690F912260>

    Model domain boundary#

    Returns the model domain boundary as a polygon. 1. Polygon in model coordinate system. 1. Polygon in latitude/longitude coordinates.

    [8]:

    ds.herbie.polygon[0]

    [8]:

    [9]:

    ds.herbie.polygon[1]
